type casting
type casting is converting the type of data from one data type to another data type.
we have two type of type casting.
1/Explict/Narrowing/manual
2/ Implicit/widening/Automatic
when we go from  BIGGER data type to SMALLER one it is called Explict/Narrowing/manual.  
when we go from SMALLER data type to LARGER data type we called it Implicit/widening/Automatic.

if statement
if else  conditions  allow us to write programs that can take decision based on some condition and provided date.

if condition
if else condition
if else of condition
nested if else condition
